    "body": "## Summary\n- Fixes #1997\n- When a shared memory buffer is consumed by multiple `T.gemm` operations with different transpose semantics, each gemm infers a different swizzle layout for the shared buffer, causing a layout conflict error\n- For MMA instructions, the swizzle layout is only a bank conflict optimization, not a correctness requirement. Skip layout inference for shared buffers that already have a layout inferred by a prior operator\n- WGMMA / TCGEN5MMA / MFMA retain strict layout enforcement since they have hard shared memory layout requirements\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Reproducer from #1997 compiles successfully\n- [x] Regression tests pass (73 passed, 1 pre-existing import error unrelated to this change)\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Introduced an operator-level layout-constraint mechanism to allow ops to declare and adjust per-buffer layout strictness during inference.\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved layout inference for matrix-multiply paths, making shared-memory buffer layouts more reliable and consistent across targets (including Hopper/WGMMA).\n* **Chores**\n  * Enhanced bookkeeping to preserve strict buffer constraint state across inference phases.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
